  "commentary": "With SPX at 6593.46 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6580 (-6150.8M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 6605 (+10213.7M), dealers are in active hedging mode—buying dips toward 6580 and preparing to sell any push toward 6605. The breakout regime with -2882.2M total GEX means dealers will amplify moves, but the proximity to that 6605 wall creates a natural magnet effect where any rally gets sold hard. Watch for volatility compression between 6580-6605, with a break above 6605 triggering dealer selling into strength and a break below 6580 forcing dealer buying that could accelerate downside.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy action between 6580 and 6605 until one of these levels breaks decisively.",
